article_title: Tenet Healthcare Hurt by Lawsuit Costs, Helped by Decline in Uninsured
article_text:
Tenet Healthcare Corp. swung to an unexpected first-quarter loss as the hospital operator increased a reserve for a potential resolution of a whistleblower lawsuit that alleges the company’s Georgia hospitals took part in a kickback scheme.

However, shares rose 4.6% to $33.10 in recent after-hours trading as per-share earnings, excluding certain one-time items, were mostly above expectations and revenue topped estimates.
